 **********Rock, Paper, Scissors Game**********

 This repository contains a Python implementation of the classic Rock, Paper, Scissors game. Play against the computer and see if you can reach the winning score!

 **********Features:**********
 User-friendly interface for choosing rock (r), paper (p), or scissors (s).
 Point system: Earn points for winning rounds and ties.
 Play until you reach the maximum score (configurable) or choose to quit.
 How to Play:

 **********Clone or download the repository.**********
 Run the Python script (python rock_paper_scissors.py).
 Follow the prompts to choose your move.
 The computer will also make a random choice.
 The winner of each round and the current score will be displayed.
 You can choose to play again after each round.

 **********Example Gameplay:**********
 Comp turn: Rock(r), Paper(p) or Scissors(s)?
 Your turn: Rock(r), Paper(p) or Scissors(s)? p
 Computer chose s
 You win!

 Comp turn: Rock(r), Paper(p) or Scissors(s)?
 Your turn: Rock(r), Paper(p) or Scissors(s)? r
 Computer chose r
 Tie!

 Final Scores: Player - 2, Computer - 1
 Thanks for playing!
 Technical Details:

 The code uses the random module to generate the computer's choice.
 A function determine_winner checks the user's and computer's choices to determine the winner or tie.
 Points are awarded based on the round outcome and stored in separate variables for the player and computer.
